TL;DR

Four agents with distinct roles — Ember (Chief of Staff, L3), Scout (Research, L2), Forge (Infrastructure, L3), and Architect (Strategy, L2) — all using MiniMax M2.5 by default.

Home / Agents

Meet Your Agents

Agent Team OS is built around a team of four AI agents, each with a distinct role and area of responsibility. They work together behind the scenes to keep your life organized, your information current, and your infrastructure running smoothly. You are the decision-maker; the agents handle the execution.

Each agent operates within a trust level that defines how much autonomy it has. Some agents can act independently on routine tasks, while others require your approval before making changes. This system ensures that you stay in control while benefiting from the agents' ability to work around the clock.

Here is your team:

Ember — Chief of Staff

Role: Daily Operations Trust Level: 3 Model: MiniMax M2.5 Focus: Coordination & Prioritization

Ember is your day-to-day coordinator. She manages the daily cadence, creates your morning reports and evening check-ins, tracks task priorities, and serves as the central point of communication between you and the other agents. If you need something adjusted, Ember is your first point of contact.

Scout — Research Specialist

Role: Information Gathering Trust Level: 2 Model: MiniMax M2.5 Focus: Research & Summarization

Scout handles deep research and information gathering. When you need to investigate a topic, evaluate options, or monitor sources for updates, Scout does the legwork. Findings are summarized and placed in Notes so you can review them at your convenience.

Forge — Infrastructure Specialist

Role: System Maintenance Trust Level: 3 Model: MiniMax M2.5 Focus: Reliability & Automation

Forge keeps the system running. He manages Syncthing synchronization, monitors scheduled tasks and backups, tracks system health, and handles the EC2 instance that powers your agent team. Forge works mostly in the background — you will rarely interact with him directly unless something needs your attention.

Architect — Strategic Planner

Role: Deep Synthesis & Analysis Trust Level: 2 Model: MiniMax M2.5 Focus: Strategic Planning & Complex Problem-Solving

Architect handles high-stakes work that requires deep reasoning — strategic planning, complex analysis, and synthesis across multiple domains. Use /model to temporarily switch to Claude Opus for tasks that benefit from maximum reasoning depth.

Model Selection

All agents use MiniMax M2.5 (openrouter/minimax/minimax-m2.5) as the default model for consistency and cost-efficiency. You can temporarily change any agent's model using the /model command in your conversation. For example, /model openrouter/anthropic/claude-opus-4.6 switches to Claude Opus for the current session. See Agent Runner for how model selection works in the agent loop.
